column3: Clinical_Visit_Date minus the date the measure was taken in units of days.
column4: To calculate when a measure was collected, you can subtract this value from the days_in_study
[0: less than 0.1%, 1: around 0.5%, 2: around 3%, 3: around 15%, 4: around 50%, 5: more than 70%]

column2: Note about database_coding field in the Clinical and Behavioural Items sheet
If the database_coding == 'Reverse Coding' that means data is saved oppsite of how it was collected.
For example p_fad_1_planning_misunderstandings variable has the options for 1 = STRONGLY AGREE; 2 = AGREE; 3 = DISAGREE; 4 = STRONGLY DISAGREE when the data is collected
However, it is saved in the databse such that: 4 = STRONGLY AGREE; 3 = AGREE; 2 = DISAGREE; 1 = STRONGLY DISAGREE
